    <item>
      <title>Guides: How-To: Delete an application from a Radius Environment</title>
      <link>https://docs.radapp.io/guides/deploy-apps/howto-delete/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://docs.radapp.io/guides/deploy-apps/howto-delete/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;h2 id=&#34;pre-requisites&#34;&gt;Pre-requisites&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/guides/deploy-apps/&#34;&gt;deployed application&lt;/a&gt; in a Radius Environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-1-delete-the-radius-application-from-the-environment&#34;&gt;Step 1: Delete the Radius Application from the environment&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can delete the Radius Application using the &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/reference/cli/rad_application_delete/&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;rad app delete&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rad app delete &amp;lt;appname&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This will delete the following resources from the Radius Environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All the resources created by Radius on the Kubernetes cluster under the &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;namespace-name&amp;gt;-&amp;lt;app-name&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; namespace&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All the resources provisioned by Recipes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-2-delete-any-cloudplatform-resources&#34;&gt;Step 2: Delete any cloud/platform resources&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AWS, Azure, Kubernetes, and any other cloud/platform resources that were deployed alongside your Radius Application and not as part of a Recipe need to be deleted as a separate step.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&#34;nav nav-tabs&#34; id=&#34;tabs-2&#34; role=&#34;tablist&#34;&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link active&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-2-azure-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-2-azure&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-2-azure&#34; aria-selected=&#34;true&#34;&gt;
    Azure
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-2-aws-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-2-aws&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-2-aws&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    AWS
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-2-kubernetes-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-2-kubernetes&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-2-kubernetes&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    Kubernetes
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;tab-content&#34; id=&#34;tabs-2-content&#34;&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade show active&#34; id=&#34;tabs-2-azure&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-2-azure-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;Azure resources can be deleted via the &lt;a href=&#34;https://portal.azure.com/&#34;&gt;Azure portal&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=&#34;https://learn.microsoft.com/cli/azure/resource?view=azure-cli-latest#az-resource-delete&#34;&gt;Azure CLI&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-2-aws&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-2-aws-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;AWS resources can be deleted via the &lt;a href=&#34;https://aws.amazon.com/console/&#34;&gt;AWS console&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/cloudcontrol/delete-resource.html&#34;&gt;AWS CLI&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-2-kubernetes&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-2-kubernetes-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;Kubernetes resources can be deleted via &lt;a href=&#34;https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/cheatsheet/#deleting-resources&#34;&gt;kubectl delete&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;/div&gt;

      </description>
